Controversial Nigerian pastor Timothy Omotoso had hired prominent Port Elizabeth defence attorney Alwyn Griebenow to represent him in the face of allegations that he sexually molested young girls at his home in Umhlanga Durban.However, that did not help him as he was slapped with a 50 year jail term for sexual assault.Omotoso of the Jesus Dominion International Church in Durban was found guilty for molesting more than 30 young girls on the pretext of rescuing them from drugs.The Nigerian evangelist came under scrutiny after his church featured on current affairs programme Special Assignment on Sunday. The programme spoke to women who claimed that they were lured into performing sexual favours for the pastor.His defense team have indicate that they will appeal against the sentence.